---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is NA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)"
  description="NA is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL (North American). It scores 2 points and means 'no' in Scottish dialect. Check which dictionary your game uses before playing NA."
  keywords="is na a scrabble word, na scrabble, na valid scrabble, na sowpods only, na not twl, scottish words scrabble, na meaning scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is NA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)",
    "description": "NA is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL. It scores 2 points and means 'no' in Scottish dialect.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-na-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is NA a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "NA is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (International/Collins dictionary). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List used in North America). NA scores 2 points (N=1, A=1) and is a Scottish dialect word meaning 'no' or 'not'. Always check which dictionary your game uses before playing NA." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why is NA not valid in TWL?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "TWL (Tournament Word List) used in North American Scrabble excludes certain regional dialect words that SOWPODS includes. NA, being a Scottish/dialectal form of 'no', didn't meet NASPA's inclusion criteria. Many dialect-specific 2-letter words are SOWPODS-only — including ZE, GI, and CH." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does NA mean in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "NA is a Scottish and dialectal English word meaning 'no' or 'not'. It appears in Scottish literature and speech as an informal negation. In SOWPODS Scrabble, it functions as a useful 2-letter play for rack management and parallel word creation." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is NA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        NA is valid in SOWPODS (International) but NOT in TWL (North American). It scores 2 points and is a Scottish dialect word meaning "no" or "not". Before playing NA in any game, confirm which dictionary your match is using — playing it in a TWL game will result in a challenge penalty.
      </p>

      <!-- Warning-Style Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-950/30 to-red-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-500/70">⚠️ Dictionary-Dependent</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">NA</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-orange-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · N=1, A=1 · Scottish for "no"</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">NA is SOWPODS-only. If you're playing in North America (TWL/NASPA rules), this word will be challenged off the board. International players can use it freely as a rack-clearing tool.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">SOWPODS ✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">International</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">TWL ✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Not Valid</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">Scottish</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Origin</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Some Words Are SOWPODS-Only</h2>

      <p>SOWPODS includes approximately 279,000 words compared to TWL's 187,000. The difference comes from regional vocabulary:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ SOWPODS Includes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">British dialect, Scottish, Australian, South African English, archaic terms, more regional words</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ TWL Excludes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Many dialect words, certain interjections, some British/Commonwealth English that hasn't entered American usage</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Playing NA in SOWPODS Games</h2>

      <p>When you're in a SOWPODS game, NA becomes a useful tactical tool:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack clearing:</span> Both N and A are common tiles (6 N-tiles, 9 A-tiles). When you're holding too many vowels or common consonants, NA lets you dump two for a fresh draw.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> NA creates crosswords effectively. Playing it alongside an existing word forms multiple scoring opportunities simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Endgame dump:</span> In tight endgames where board space is limited, a 2-letter word can be the difference between playing out and getting stuck with tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Other SOWPODS-Only 2-Letter Words</h2>

      <p>NA isn't alone — several other useful 2-letter words work only in international play:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">NA</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">2pts · SOWPODS</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">ZE</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">11pts · SOWPODS</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">GI</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">3pts · SOWPODS</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">CH</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">7pts · SOWPODS</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Important Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Always confirm your dictionary <span class="text-white font-medium">before the game starts</span>. Online platforms usually state which dictionary is in use. In tournaments, it's announced at the start. Playing a SOWPODS-only word in a TWL game loses your turn.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ze-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZE a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (11 Points)</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ew-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EW a Scrabble Word? Dictionary Validity Check</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-only-in-sowpods/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Only in SOWPODS: International Scrabble Exclusives</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
